      • testArrayBasedList

        public void testArrayBasedList()
        Tests that a ArrayBasedList is constructed correctly. ArrayBasedList of any generic type should be not null and empty, which implies a size of 0. Test method for CSC216ArrayList.CSC216ArrayList().

      • testAddIntE

        public void testAddIntE()
        Tests adding elements to an empty CSC216ArrayList. Then tests adding elements to the front, middle, and back of a CSC216ArrayList. The size and contents should be checked after each insertion. Additionally, the bounds of the list should be checked and null elements should not be added to the list. Finally, test that the ArrayList with an initial capacity of 10 grows when an 11th element is added. Test method for CSC216ArrayList.add(int, java.lang.Object).

      • testRemoveInt

        public void testRemoveInt()
        Tests that elements are correctly removed from the front, middle, and back of an ArrayList. Removing the last element should leave an empty list. The bounds are checked for the appropriate exceptions. Test method for CSC216ArrayList.remove(int).

      • testSetIntE

        public void testSetIntE()
        Tests setting an element in an empty list, the bounds of the list when using the set() method, and setting an element at the front, middle, and back of the list. The set() method is also passed null. Test method for CSC216ArrayList.set(int, java.lang.Object).

      • testGetInt

        public void testGetInt()
        Main get() functionality is tested in the other test methods. This method will focus on testing the exceptions associated with bounds. Test method for CSC216ArrayList.get(int).

      • testIntegerMethods

        public void testIntegerMethods()
        Main functionality of ArrayBasedList is tested in this test method. This method will focus on testing the the previously tested methods, but instead with number objects instead of strings, as previously done.
